SAPS management briefed the Community Safety Committee on the status of an investigation into firearms stolen from Norwood Police Station. The number of missing firearms has now increased to 175. eNCA's Barry Bateman was there and filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Further investigations have revealed more firearms have been stolen from the Norwood police station. The initial tally of 158 has now risen to 175 and this may grow as the probe continues. READ: Gauteng legislature inspects Norwood SAPS The Gauteng Legislature's Community Safety Committee conducted an oversight visit to the police station to get answers. In the briefing, police pinned the blame on an evidence store clerk, who took his own life last year. * eNCA's Barry Bateman reports.